#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
eval-bench-audit.py — Phase 8 cross-cutting auditor for the eval/bench/QA layer.

Runs every time the user asks "what's the state of my eval/bench layer?"
or can be invoked in a pre-push / CI cron to detect drift, dirty state,
missing artifacts, and broken wiring.

This script is INTENTIONALLY side-effect-free: it only reads state, computes
scores, and prints a single human-readable report. It never modifies any
repo. It is the SSOT for "is the eval/bench/QA layer healthy?".

Usage:
    python eval-bench-audit.py            # human-readable table
    python eval-bench-audit.py --json     # machine-readable JSON for CI
    python eval-bench-audit.py --ci       # exit 1 if any score < threshold

Author: Phase 8 DAG extension (2026-06-23)
"""
